arm, he saw that she had everything like that, and the chimney - they seemed - very - I don't know whether I should be saying this, but the - chimney - would - when the windy weather would come, it would - you could see it moving, it was so well built. Th
e
 - the kitchen chimney. Yes. And the grate was a large grate with a boiler one side with a brass tap on it and a large oven the other side and a - a pit under the fireplace and we only once a week - we rose the ashes as it were, you see. Just once a week.
 Once a week. So father lit the fire, the ashes went down you see, that's how we had rose there and sometimes the men would light it for us, you see. It was a through and through business you see.
