\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, but there is some - there
 are - yes, a difference in - we saw it - 'cos I remember tying and untying the old bull every - everyday - when the other cows were coming in the bull would come with them, tying him, this sort of thing, two big old horns straight, he was as docile as a 
l
amb. But then - the others I remember - come from Aberdare Bach father bought them. We had - I - I know specially of two, we had to kill them. So the only thing was to do was to fatten them there. And we had to kill them there. I remember seeing a cow - b
u
ll being killed on the farm. You don't know how they killed them do you? We won't say that, not now. But I've seen it. People used to come round, everything was in order mind you see. The butcher, our own butcher would come and do it. David Evans the butc
h
er you see. Then there was Gwilliams at - Gwilliam - he'd come. Evan Lewis would come after. Yes. And that's a thing that - I can - I've often said that if people only listen to the old people - we did have a case of foot and mouth there. And he isolated 
her. And got - put plenty of bedding under her do you see, and cleared it and plent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5642835\charrsid15934717 y of lime - as well. Washed the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
 - the feet, because it was the foot it was you see, and the mouths - shut completely. It shuts completely, the cow can't eat. That's what's wrong do you see. And then he - somehow or other he was putting mother used to make her own ointment. From }{
