\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 With actually dressing or eating your food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, we had to because our -
 our dresses were all buttons down the back, there was no zipp then do you see, and you had about eighteen buttons down your back. You would do a couple - well will you finish it for me, you see. Yes. And put your hair - we put one another's hair up, I co
uld hold my apron up in my hair, it was that - just like today's, the long fashion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You would help one another like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would the younger children help the older children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And - we used to bath one another, always, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
It all depend the weather. If it was winter it was in the kitchen by the fire. Although - when the - when the electric works came there we didn't have a bathroom. We used to bath in the upper room of the
 two rooms you see, because you never knew who was coming to the door do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you lock the door when you bathed in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, there was no locking then. No. I don't think there was a lock on anything, only the back and front door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would people walk in and out while you were bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no. No. That's definite. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - pretty often I must say and I can tell you when - when we went to the well - we used to cross the brook with two l
ittle plants, I don't know who put the planks there, but it was there I saw them, but we kiddies in the summer we'd put the jacks under the well, we had off our shoes and stockings off and we paddled. So we never had dirty feet. No. No. And - well we - we
 didn't know when to go home, we enjoyed it so much, and - and catch tiddlers you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often would you have to go for water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh practically every day in the summer. Yes. Some end of the day, go before it was too hot, or late in the evening see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you have to be very economical with the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well yes, we knew - watched how it - you know, we had to be carrying now. Oh now, don't be too - too flush with that it was you see. And sometimes - the cask water out there, we had two
 casks there, they'd freeze over. You had to crack the ice to get it, and - we'd to use a bowl with a handle, I don't know whether you've seen them today, but there's one in the old home now. Yes. What we call a vol. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about bathing then, you'd use a lot of water for bathing wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often would you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - it was - every wee - weekend for sure. Yes, yes. Oh yes, we daren't go to chapel on Sunday dirty. No indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And you would bath each other would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh yes. We'd bath together do you see. Yes. Oh say when you're ready and I'll wash your back or anything, I'll help you to - dry one another's hair do you see. Yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, and the - the wash house where we did our washing, there was a hug}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5642835\charrsid15934717 e}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
 bench there do you see and a huge boiler and the fireplace there as well, and there was a line - for - across the wall, there, it was back to back from the kitchen, the kitchen as well, that wall was always warm, we always had towels there
 drying as well do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - every - at the week - whatever. Yes. We had - I was saying - always a pinafore, we used to wear a pinafore to go to chapel, to go to Sunday school, pinafore, white pin
afore with - this - like openwork embroidery on it, little frill. But - to go to school, we had - lilac or navy blue and white pinafores with tie ups on the shoulders, square - and a tie up on each side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes, we had to - eight o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. She saw that - she saw that we washed ourselves clean - if you were too dirty we had to wash altogether, all over, and
 then - and - upstairs - was the landing, and the five doors - came out onto the landing, and she - mo - mother, when we'd gone upstairs she'd bring the candlestick and put it on the landing. Now then, that candle must last so you mustn't - she'd light it
,
 are you all in bed? Then - all doors were open do you see, get to bed and then of course she'd - she come - I'm coming up to fetch the candle, I can give you five minutes more. So - oh if we talked too much see a scramble to get in bed - while it was lig
ht, because she took the candle down. Yes. And our supper - was always a Welsh cake. Yes, a Welsh cake, one or two, what you wanted you see. And then - and we - a jug of milk and each one had a cup or half cup of the milk. That was our supper always.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What age would you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I don't remember my mother undressing me. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you share the bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. We slept two in a bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would be in the bed with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well the - the one who slept with me three years was Gwen. Gwenllian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who else would be in the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only me. That's all. Only we two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only one bed, you can't remember what the bedroom arrangement was for the whole family because you were a lot weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm. Well - ther
e was a - I know my mother and father were - we - they were sleeping above the dairy. Then there was - there was a bed with two of us in above the kitchen. Then the large bedroom had two beds in it do you see. And when we were small we slept there. Have t
wo in a bed do you see. Four of us would be sleeping there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where would your brother be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
He'd be in the little single bedroom. But - I - you know, you're asking now do you see things that - alters with - with - girls getting married do yo
u see, into - so - so - then of course - the bedroom where there were two beds in it that's where my brother slept in one bed and the two servant men in the other bed, so they were together - that way. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they be in the house then the servant men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, those two, but there was another servant man outside. No difference in them. They had - he had a lovely bed where he was as well do you see. And beautiful oak floors there. 'Cos they noticed that when the power station came, and they said 
it was wonderful woodwork, the power station - there's no home there now do you see, it's gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was taken over was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes, taken over - the power station's been built there now do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you have to get out or had you all gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh - my brother, we left my brother there and his wife and the little boy. And we - I - I got married you see. And mother retired and - and came to live next - but she retired before I was married, she bought the house, but that - it was idea
l for about three years I think before she went to live to it. You know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
We - the power station now, they wanted to try out the electricity. Our farm was the guineas pig. We had the - electricity through the cow sheds, the stables and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Somewhere about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was quite a long time ago then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. Yes. 'Cos I think it was 1903 the foundation stone of the works was bought. And the electric works, well I was passing up - I left Hougham school 
- about ten and a half I was, of an - ordinary school you know, then I went to Mill Street High Grade. And - we used to pass over there and they'd - the works was built in that period, you see. And then I came home, as I say went to dairy school, well we 
did our own chaffing. I don't know - when I look back I think my - I must say I never thought my father was such a man as he was. You know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You don't realize when you're young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no. It never dawned on me, yes, what - what they had to do - to 
- get on to do what they did do, well he had a wonderful - mincing machine, to do this - and - and everything like that. Well he had a chaffing machine after. And a chaffing loft. Everybody about people - they'll say this about them and my mother always s
p
oke of them whatever my mother asked for she had. They were good, yes. I must say - very good that way. Yes. Wonderful. I remember mother - was very - she was very fond of flowers and I remember - counting as many as fourteen kinds of - roses there, with 
us do you see, we grew enough apples for the year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And you had pears you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, as well do you see, father used to graft. And in his later years used to graft the trees - oh that was another thing really. He'd - cut a branch off a tree.
 Take a branch off another tree, get small pieces like that, then he'd make a - a - the - the cutting would be flat, he'd put - earth there, manure, cows manure, then he'd put four or five pieces of this little branch of other trees in there, bind it with
 
any old flannel, cotton, linen, mackintosh, anything whatever. And with time he used to ask - come here. He'd put his glasses on, he couldn't see very good, he'd lift me up, can you see anything there? Yes. What? Four pieces. How - how many do you see? Fo
ur. Any green in them? Yes. How many leaves? And so on and so on. Right. They'd caught. Yes. And - and we'd lovely orchards. Yes. Yes. And plums. And I'm awfully fond of plums and we used to have yellow and - the Victoria plums then. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have to pick them or would that work be done by the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh - we'd pick them. Yes. Remember my mother - I'd go up the apple trees, and mother or one of the others would hold their apron and you'd drop the apples one at a time, and put them in a bas
ket, not to - yes, always. Oh I climbed them like a monkey. Climbed the hay - haystack like anybody else. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have your own flour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Flour for bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well we - we would buy it back sometimes but no we didn't 
grow much of that. No. No. But we grew enough to have oats for the - horses, for the cows, yes, and the straw after - we'd put it through the chaffing machine and mix it with the hay, you see. But the rougher straw was kept for bedding, do you see. Yes. A
n
d - now you want to know how we did our machine for - treading the chaffing. It - it was by hand the chaffing was done first. Afterwards, but when it was made I don't know. We had a circular thing like this in the middle of the yard. The hou - the house i
s
 there, the barns - cow house, barns, stable, mincing she'd, above it was the chaffing room and there's like a storeroom for hay, after there. Well now - through that - there was a tube coming down through this and I don't know how it came, but it came un
d
er the ground - around tube, and there was a piece here just like a - how do you call those now, you see them on the seashore when the tide - yes, like a bollard you know, there's another name, capstan, that's it, and - and there was a - that was iron, an
d it turned like this, it was turning, and along this was a large pole across here, at both sides, well we'd - hitch a horse here. Now we children had to go around that all the time. The horse pulled this, you see, but we -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You had to lead the horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, not lead it, just - keep it going. Touch it like this with a - little bit of stick, or something, or - or stop it, whoa, stop, and then of course - while it was going the chaffing is going on upstairs, and there's a window there and my brother wo
uld tap the window, right. Didn't want to go around no more do you see? And then when it - when the chaff - we had plenty of chaff father cut a hole in the bottom of the floor and put a tube of canvas down - the chaff was swept into that hole, down into t
h
e mincing room. And the mixing was going on there. You see and - and that's how we did our chaffing, but I remember - chaffing coming there, we chaffed by electricity. We were the first to do it. Yes, it was the first - yes, and it was - very - oh well we
 
couldn't help looking at it, everybody, they came there from everywhere to see it. Yes. And I - I - I don't know - yes, well - yes all along then. Yes, well - you can see - eleven to twelve, fourteen, something like that do you see. But - it was the first
 farm to - really use electric. Yes, yes. I remember the searchlights coming there, trying it out to show the whole area. Yes, a huge searchlight. Yes. Oh the searchlight was lit, we could go to bed without any lamps or candles or anything you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you think then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh well, of course it was wonderful. And of course we could see it was such - well much less work do you see. Yes, yes. Yes. And with time of course there was such dust from the work we were allowed to go to the works to get the
 water from the tap. Waterworks - after. Then we didn't go very much, only for the occasional - lot of water, when - if we were butter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5642835\charrsid15934717 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717  butter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5642835\charrsid15934717 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 making we wanted the well water. That was clean. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever have the water laid on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. NO
. Unless they had it after we moved away or something you see. 'Cos the - the - the house went, but the policemen were looking after the works lived there after we - yes, so I - I can't - I - remember going to see the old farm, it was empty. And all our w
indows were diamonds. Diamond shaped. Iron yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were a little girl where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Kitchen and the - upper room. Do you see, the - we - the upper rooms 'cos we went up a step, do you see, from the - the kitchen wa
s here, the dairy was here, the kitchen's here, then we went there there was a little - hallway or passage do you see, little passage there, a hallway there and a door to it, and door there's a large room here. Large dining, there was a door there, large 
dining table there, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would you eat in that upper room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well it was usually on the Sunday. Or of course - we used to cook two dinners, we'd cook a dinner midday, for the farm hands and mother and father and me an my sister and the lau
ndry, the woman who was washing for us, but - and in the - in the evening - there was Eunice and Florrie and - Ellen and Gwen would come home, they'd want their dinner after do you see. Then perhaps they'd have it in the other room 'cos the serving men wa
nted their tea there. Or sometimes we used to put tea out to them. Yes, take a basket and - a huge - jug of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about when you were a little girl before Gwen and the others had gone to work, where would you have your meals then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh in the k
itchen. Yes. In relays you see. Yes. 'Cos by the time the - the different serving men and my brother, my father got out, it was time we could have breakfast now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How early would they have theirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh we were - the men - the man was coming to fetc
h the milk there before seven. So we had to do the milking before then do you see. And now - I wake - when my sister up her I been - I wake about half past five. I - I - and gone back to the old style do you see. I've been so used to it - and then - then 
-
 we would go - have a rest, I'd read - in the afternoon. And I remember my mother going - failing you know, she'd sit down now, read this out for me. She'd - I - I read many a book. I'd read the Welsh Singer right through for her. And - I'd read another -
 Rhys Lewis perhaps Enoch Huws, all those books you see. Perhaps it was if she'd had a nice sermon on Sunday, read the chapter, I'd read the chapter for her do you see, and she'd be darning or sewing, she was busy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were a little girl, whe
n you were having your meals, your father and your brother and the men, they'd have theirs first would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you mother be up making the breakfast for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, she was there - saying what to do and seeing to this, that and the other, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Then you other children would have your meal then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. Yes. Then - then - then - then of course we had ours 'cos we're going to school, my brother was going to school, walk to Pontypridd mind. Three and a - three and a half miles, every day. Did it for three and a half years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You wouldn't come home in the dinner hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh dear no. Yes, we had to take our lunch. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the kitchen and the dairy. Mm. In the dairy we did the - did the cooking, the making. Yes, yes.
