\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, I do - I was punished before now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, going - she sent me round when I was young, very young mind - to go and collect eggs from the - from these different ne
sts around there, we - we weren't keeping those - other chickens, what do you call it chickens, pedigree chickens at all, the ordinary - I went and - and she was - she wanted to go to town, and I - I think she wanted the eggs to go to town with her do you
 
see, so of course - I put the - basket down, and - father always put a - we had swing and a seesaw, always, just - so I went and sat on the swing and had a good couple of swings, I forgot about the eggs, forgot about the time and all. Here's my mother com
i
ng calling - oh - all right. She didn't go to Pontypridd. And - she was going to fetch - a new - new frock for me, so I was to have a new rigout, I was without it. For the few - for a few weeks, of course I had it in due time but I didn't have it then. Mm
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would she smack you or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Rarely. Rarely. Oh telling was enough. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only your mother, your father never would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did you feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well it wasn't coming to me do you see, that's the - that's the feeling, isn't it? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You didn't think she should do it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh, that wore off. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your father, would he show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He wouldn't know of it. No. I don't know what they said behind our ba
cks. My mother never - never to us, no. Mm. We are like that. I - well I went to see a woman last Saturday night, I haven't seen her for two years and I understood that she hasn't been over the door for two years, and she used to do a lot of work for me w
h
en I was in my own home do you see, Mrs Luther Lewis, oh she looks poorly, I've been saying I'm going down and they said - when you - I can't walk to good you see, well when are you coming to see Mrs Lewis, give us a ring they said, and we'll come and - w
e
'll get somebody to fetch you down, I was rather of independent spirit and I must try to walk that much, so I went down Saturday night, I went down Saturday night. Oh and it's glad she was to see me. And I could see by here you know and I - and oh dear, I
 
thought to meself, I didn't know what to say, I couldn't say she's looking well, 'cos she's been worn down, she's gone to nothing. But I could see her wetting her mouth, she wanted a kiss from me. Indeed. I give her a kiss and she - 'cos she was - she's a
 
dear old soul with me, I must say. She used to go to three houses she used to go to the Goulton's. Oh Mrs Goulton wanted this this done and she wanted a everything done. She'd go next door to Mrs Pritchard - I don't know whether you've heard of her, she's
 - chairman of the Pontypridd magistrates, she'd go there - that one was very exacting in all ways. But I can go to Mrs Jenkins I can do what I like. As long as she did it. And she did it well fair play for her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were young if you had any worries could you share them with your father, would you tell him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh I don't remember sharing them at all with him. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They wanted obedience didn't they. And they had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brother and your sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well how do you mean now? They'd say we'd have to listen wouldn't we, to your elders yet you see, yes. Well that's how I brought my own little children up, I r
emember Ruth and Anne would try competitive meetings, one would - win a shilling, the other would win sixpence, but they had nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5642835\charrsid15934717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 pence each going home, you know, and that's the spirit is still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would your mother and father say that you could hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Leave them alone. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh I don't know, pity they weren't here to say now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - I thi
nk they could see we were heading in the right direction. Yes. I think they were happy. Because, we didn't bring trouble to them, as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Chapel going. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
And I think - oh dear anwyl, you'd have to have your tongue scrubbed. Wouldn't we. I remember saying one - I don't remember what the word was but I did say a curse word I suppose, and of course - and we had a porch
 to the house in the front and a porch on the back, and I went to hide, I didn't want my mother to see me. And of course - they were coming from there, and what are you doing there? And of course it was coming out I had to say - to say what I had done. I 
don't remember what the word was it's so far back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What would they tell you then, would you get punished then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well of course I'd be - I'd be without a lot or something. Yes. 'Cos we - we'd go to chapel and my mother'd be going to chapel with us.
 Chapel played a big part in our lives you know, and - she'd tell us now - mother couldn't walk as quick as we could, we'd run like blazes only have a penny. And she'd give us a penny, now go to Gwilym Thomsa for a pennyworth of butterscotch. And we'd got
 -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would a birthday be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
In just that - and that's all, what I was telling you you know that - an egg for breakfast. And - just a few presents flying around of course, no cards, I don't remember ever having - there we
ren't any birthday cards then do you see. No, no we wouldn't. No. And perhaps some - somebody would come visitors you see, your mother's sisters would come the - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have something special to eat other than the egg for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - perhaps - if - pancakes was a very great favourite, you know, on a winter birthday it would be that you see, but in the summer it would be more like - trifle or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. We'd - perhaps a - a rig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 out or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Anybody to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - I remember - we used to have a ni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 ce of ours used to come regular because she's the same age as me do you see. Yes. And she lived not - not very far away.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, only - we had our Christmas dinner of course, it was the farm life we had, we had to see to everything do you see as - as ordinary day do you see, but we had a jolly Christmas dinner
. Yes. Mm. I've seen the plum pudding that my mother - used the - the same basin every year since I remember, and they still have it in the old home do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have presents at Christmas or stockings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. You give presents to
 one another. And - I remember - always used to have a - a parcel used to come on Christmas Eve, and that came from my mother's sister, she remembers us every one. I had a tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 set and another would have a doll do you see. I remember the tea set with little vi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 lets on it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A little one was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no, it was size - you could use it. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did she live a long way away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Porth. Yes. Yes. Yes. Well she lived in the old area where they were living - where they were born you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, an organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who in the family would play the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well my - oldest sister, and - Jane, she had a lot of music lessons, so did Ellen. Ellen went on and she used to play
 in the - festivals regularly for years she did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well myself of course, I did a little bit of music but - had a voice training. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were telling me you had three years voice training?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Finishing when you were about twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. With - a man from Freforest, in Cil - Cilfynydd he lived first. That was the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It must be something in the air in Cilcynydd that makes you all good singers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - well I don't know, up there we had - that's where Ellen went to have her music lessons. It was our Sunday school teacher, he was the organist at the time in chapel, told my sister - she said, I'd like to learn. Well you children
 should learn, he said, 'cos I won't always be had here, you'll have to take the music - to the instrument yourself and - and I'm away at chapel. And so she listened to him and she went - she said, try - there's a little man, he's a conductor - for this, 
t
hat and the other, he's got a choir - go and see what he'll do. And indeed he took her on. And she was with him for years. And - at the time - he was talking to her about - artists, she said, well my sister next to me, she sings very well at home, this th
at and the other. Bring her up some day. And I had a trial there and I went on from there. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you do much singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I did a lot of singing during the war. First world war, yes. I remember used to go around then to the different chapels. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 Yes. Solo, yes, duets, quartet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
s, yes. Well - on - soldiers on embarkation leave I did an awful lot of those. All voluntaries you see. Yes, I remember the minister Evenezar, The Reverend Edwin Jones from Kenfighill, he came there, and - they used to come 
home on leave, unawares, and the short - time was short, he had to go round to see who he could get to get a concert up before tomorrow night sort of thing, because they - wanted to give them a concert, a farewell concert and present them with anything th
a
t they would be - having and - he's come home and he's said - and then he's come home and asked mother, and mother said, Welsh she spoke of course all you see, and oh you don't want her again. They're surely tired of hearing her. They're never tired of he
a
ring her. I've seen it myself, I know. Then - we are sure of a full house if we can say Miss Morgan is coming. And - yes, I took the - you couldn't - I couldn't get in, it was squeeze in through the crowd to get in when I got there, 'cos of course I could
n't go in time perhaps because - it would - we had to do it early, it was milking time finishing, and walk all the way there see, two and a half miles perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was there anyone else who sang, you said your father had a good voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, but he didn't - only - only precentos he was, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the home did you make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh yes, very often, yes. Yes. My brother didn't seem to take much in the music line. No, no. But my mother - she had a voice, she - well - I could
 imitate her now but it would be a bit laughable so I won't do it. Mrs Morgan, yes, we were going round, yes, and then - mother'd come in now and - and perhaps the preacher would come in - ydych in gwybod y peth ar peth? Odw. Canwych ini nante, yes. On a 
Sunday night, yes. And - after chapel. Now we go back into the other room, the dining room and we'd a family service after. Usually, yes. With sleeping there, they'd be there for the weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you all be singing round the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, we woul
d pract - all of us had pretty decent voices. Yes. Ellen - was - she sang contralto. And Eunice sang contralto. Florrie couldn't sing at all, see. She was - lip - lip serving on our language she had to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Hide the thimble was about the most we had. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no, nothing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, plenty. We had a lovely lot of books. And established you know, 'cos most of them 
Welsh books you see, yes. Yes, yes. We had all Pantycelyn, Islwyn and those do you see. And Geiriadur Charles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And you mentioned you had Rhys Lewis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, Rhys Lewis, Enoch Huwa and - Gwen Thomas - all those, yes. And I remember reading - the 
Window in Front, John Halifax Gentleman, quite a lot of things I can't - I can't remember them all now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about newspapers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. No, only the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 ontypridd Observer, used to have on Saturday, used to have that. And perhaps we might buy the - the South Wales - Daily News it was then, the - and it's amalgamated with the Western Mail - in later years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, we used to have - the Trysorfa Fach. And it was edited by the Revered Thomas Levy, Professor Levy's father.
 My mother was the one who took the first edition of it. Yes. And if I'm not mistaken my sister's got still - still got it - in the old home. The first - and that was very far back mind. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Reading? Yes, chapters. Chapters ahead. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did they ever read aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
And I'll tell you this much, we tried my father in his later years - this is later - in very later years of course at the farm - in 1913 then - we tried him in the book of Ps}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 lms, 
only two pslams we had to help him. He knew them all. Yes. Yes, that's it. Yes, yes. As sure as I'm sitting here. And my father could tell you where to do do you see but I can't. I know quite a lot mind, you know, but - not half enough, but - I couldn't s
ay that way. He was surely eighty-seven when we did it, when we tried him out. Yes. And hymn - the hymn book was - was - you know, his favourite as well you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You mentioned that he used to read to you sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes. And - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he read to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, mother read a lot herself as well do you see, but he'd read to us when mother had gone to chapel with the oldest girls do you see, and read to his younger children. See we were a large family - do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There would be a big gap between the oldest and the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, that's it, yes. And by the time they the older ones were in chapel but we younger ones do you see, Eunice was rather delicate, the youngest, well Floorrie was lip - lip language do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Deaf and dumb was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Not - you can't say she was really deaf and dumb, she came to talk wonderfully. Yes. But - she wouldn't say - me - I'm the same as you. Me same as you. You know, she'd - she'd - her own - was operated on her for one -
 and he said that's all I can do - at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. The eve - on the even of the - the funeral we always had a service. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the house. In the house, in - yes, in the - usually in th
e dining room, the largest room in the house do you see. Yes. Oh and they'd be there from everywhere. Yes. And we had lovely singing, you'd hear it across the fields. We sang as if - it was an ordinary service do you see but - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would go to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
All the family would be there. We'd all be there do you see, yes, and then all the relations and - and the church members used to come do you see, the deacon, perhaps four or five deacons would be there you see, and all take part, it was a pray
er meeting do you see, yes. Yes, and we'd sing, once, twice or three times perhaps if not more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about when you were children, would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, oh dear, yes. Yes. Oh dear yes, we were in - we had to go and be choir too. And I remember g
oing sad to my mother's - my father's home where he was born, and going there, and this is - this was a palace of a place, a large place, oh a big old beams you know, and they'd come from everywhere there. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You remember the funeral then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh
 yes, remember him - it was my father's brother it was. And he was the - the eldest and chief deacon in Bryntirion chapel, and of course - when Bryntirion - they - they lent money to the - quite a lot of money, and of course the Jubillee of Bryntirion cha
pel it was he paid all the debt you see, until he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 At Porth isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, no. In Bryntirion, Lantwit Fardre, yes, that's my father's people you see, and - and it was my father's brother that was. And I remember when he died - my - my brother
 that had gone there to - he had adopted him to you see, came over and said that Uncle William had died, father's father, oh - come on children, get ready}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 quick, my mother said, and Eleanor and I had to go and - I don't know, we - I don't think Eleanor was more than about twelve, and of course I was - younger then you - eight, perhaps eight and a half, we walked from our}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717  house up to Bryntirion, and ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
d to go and tell the deacons there that Uncle had passed away, and that they could announce the Jubilee that
 the debt was paid - on his death. Yes, I remember that, as - as a child. Then we all went to the funeral. And - we were dressed in black like robes. Yes. And I remember being a naughty girl. Going to the chapel in the side seat there and I was seen putti
ng something in my mouth. It was a lump of sugar. I took it from somewhere see. And I remember my mother seeing me, looking like that at me very sharp. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would be there at that funeral then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh my mother and father. We were all as a family there. Yes. Yes. And - coaches do you see. Yes. Coaches they were then. Drawn }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717  horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 drawn. Yes. Two horses on each one. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have mourning clothes, all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, yes, all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 For an uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. For father's - yes. A
nd my father, well I - I know - of course mother - they were very well to do, do you see, and so of course we - we carried it all out to the - to the letter, and we kept in black for a twelve months.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, all the lot of us. You see that was the fashion do you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have special black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, it would be, yes, and we used to go to the dressmaker in - in Pontypridd, Hughes's, Hughes's there, mother give the order, want a dress - a frock each for us. And perhaps
 we'd wear black and white coats and I remember having a black and white coat, yes, with white buttons, yes, yes yes. And my mother'd have a - black bordered handkerchief, yes. Yes, they - black border for mother, but we girls would have little ones with 
a
 little edging - embroidered edge. Yes, I remember talking to a person, she died about two years ago now, she was ninety-one, and she said do you remember the time we used to go to funerals, she said, and I - we all - if we wanted a pin it had to be a bla
ck one. They were so keen, oh yes. Yes, yes. Yes. I've got a black bordered neck thing now. In - a jabot, that we used to put inside the - the dress like do you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your father's funeral in 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, that was a very large funeral. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would attend that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
We all went. All of us went, yes. And - mother, we all went. And all the - well the - the - his first family, they came - Hannah and her husband came, Mary and - and - Frank came. They were all there, and - fo
od was prepared in the chapel. Yes. We boiled the ham, and had it sliced and made into ham there do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would have the food then in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Anybody. Free for all you see, yes, everybody. And they'd - the chapel people would do it yo
u see of course, they would - yes, they'd do it yes, but we - we provided it, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 That was rather nice wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, well of course - the people came a distance, they had to come by - horse and trap do you see, or coach do you see, 
there were no buses then. No cars. No cars had come. I remember seeing the first car coming down through the village. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember old Doctor Price?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I wouldn't remember him, no. But he was with my mother - and the first four ch
ildren, with my - my own mother, do you see, but he was with my father's first wife. Yes. Yes. And he used to come there the first thing - he used to come in his regalia, yes, the first thing he did was take his - his bonnet off, that was the old hairy bo
nnet and put it on the chest of drawers, and it was silk lined with red, beautiful - beautiful thing, he was a funny old fine fellow but - mother was right when she saw him come in through the door. - Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He was the family doctor was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You don't remember him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, no. Yes, then. And if you'd go to the surgery - well whoever went there there was a saucer of - of lump sugar on the table, and he would say, take sugar, go on. Any children could take some sugar. No, no they wouldn't now No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He was living near you wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Llantwitsant. But he was in - he was in the Llantwit Fardre parish you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We go with mother perhaps do you see if 
mother went she took one or two of us with her. I remember going to Aberdare, with mother when I was a very small child, little tot, going to see an aunt of ours - she was an old lady do you see in her - well, with her bonnet you know and flannel apron an
d everything, you know, and - her - her daughters there, and mother'd go up and when she'd get out at the station, there - there - she would order a hansom cab, because we used to take a basket with a dozen eggs, perhaps a Welsh - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 Caerphilly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717  cheese, a whole
 one, our own make and that you see. And - if she was taking one of us with her then, and I remember this - I went with her, and a little poke bonnet fur edged and fur on the edge of the cape, in blue. And I must have been a pretty kiddy or something, wel
l
 - after spending the afternoon there we came back, Aunty Jane brought us back, the big daughter of the lady we were visiting brought us back and of course people hardly got - they was in the station in plenty of time, we had plenty of time, they were tal
k
ing and talking. My mother said where's Ruth. The train was coming, where's Ruth? Came into - I was out on the platform - with my hand in another man's hand in his pocket. Oh I was - I was just there - and I remember my mother going - come here, what do y
ou want there? But in Welsh she said it see. I was saying, if it wasn't for my mother seeing me just then goodness knows where I'd have been. Yes. About four, four and a half I could have been \{ILLEGIBLE\} Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you frightened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes I was, and they told me after that man, you didn't know who he was. Oh, they drummed it home to me I can tell you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were a bit young you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, young and - and - I - I suppose I was exceptionally pretty. You see. And ringlets. Yes, very fair c
omplex - a nice auburn do you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you ever go out shopping, would you be taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Rarely. Rarely. Our mother did the shopping - and it was delivered - well we went to fetch it do you see, yes. We bought our tea by the - tw
enty pounds, you know, just in - one large - yes, and the sugar we bought. It wasn't cube as we've got now, nor granulated, it was the old loaf. Do you remember the - yes, now, it was a - like a - a tower, cone shaped. It was tall - quite a tall thing, an
d we had a - a machine to cut that. Yes. Cut it and cut it into slices, and then from that into smaller pieces. Yes, we never had whole sugar at all, no. And then we - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 Demerara}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717  we'd have after but the - that - the lump sugar came - in - packed in a very deep blue paper, wrapped - stuck round it you know. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever go out with just your father?
