d man do you see, and of course - when he came down to Treforest to live he went to Saron chapel, the Presbyterian, then he came down to Upper Boar because we were a little church and he could see that a - quite a little band of workers there, and so he t
o
ok to us, do you see, and that was - oh I don't remember what it was - I was only a girl, seventeen, eighteen, nineteen, and that's when I went to have lessons with him do you see. So - and afterward - I left after my music after - when I was twenty-one. 
I thought, oh, I'll not get into anything but - I did go to sing doing a concert or two, I sung with Mr Harry Lewis Nelson, with him do you see. That was wartime again you see.
