y husband ever came on the scene. There was a man by the name of David Strudlin, in Llantwit, and he was interested in music, so he used to come down and teach us in the kitchen - with the organ you see, and then he'd teach us and we'd go - then we'd go t
o
 the Ynys Farm where the - these other children were living, our next door neighbours, and there we'd - we'd go there and have a practice as well. There was a piano there, and the older daughter played the piano. But my sister played the organ with us you
 see, until we did - that was - beginning of the - of the singing festival, and the singing all together, we were all - joining in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And you were big families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were quite a lot together weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. And we learnt our catechism after do you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would teach you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 This Mr Strudlin, or our own parents would know it you see and then teach us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of games would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the house you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You said you played on the seesaw and on the swing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. And - and - hopscotch, skipping. Skipping, - yes, yes. Quite a - that's the only games you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I don't remember getting so very dirty. 'Cos I think if I wa
s a young girl when the power station was built I'm sure we'd have been like colliers, 'cos when that work - when the works came, we couldn't put our washing out. Had to wash it a first - a second time, often with the - the smoke and - the dust falling do
 you see. Yes, yes. 1903 I think the foundation stone was put, if I remember rightly, I'm not far wrong I know, until they - it was very clean before, you could roll about in the grass and you - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It took your fields then didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, 
yes, yes, yes. And I remember - talking about the winter - I remember going mother telling us children - it was wintertime - to go over the yard and go through the gate of the hendra, the hendra field we called it, and look - look along that way, we looke
d
 the length of the field and we'd see the horse and cart there full of mangolds going to give the cows food because they couldn't have the grass, the snow was higher than the cart - horse and cart. And it had - it had blown it had - what do you call it - 
d
rift - yff we say in Welsh, I know more Welsh than English see. Yes. And I remembered seeing that that's one of the first memories of seeing snow, a depth of snow. Yes, yes. And all our fields you see, we had names on every field. We had names on every co
w. Mmm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What happened when the power station came in 1903?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We kept on farming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You kept the cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. And of course that's when we had Ynys Lynn Farm joined on. We had to go across the river you see. Across the river. I remember I 
used - I'd go down the river to call the cows home. Go down the island as we called it there and we'd shout, dewch, dewch, you know, and they'd come, through the river, up and milk them, as well as waiting for the cows to come I'd start - I was practicing
 
singing, I was young then. Yes, and the - and the river there you see and the row of trees and our trees and - it would be nothing for to see a couple of neighbours, she's down there today. Yes, yes. I little knew that see. I was practicing something I wa
s going to sing in the night or something you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would that be the rive Taff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, the River Taff, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They'd come across the river would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, they'd come on their own, yes. Once they'd hear your voice it was milking time,
 they were ready, their udders were full do you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no. Only the people in the next farm. Yes. Or somebody who - came to chapel you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I don't know, - mother kept us to ourselves. We were - we were plenty of company ourselves see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did they discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I don't remember. No, I don't know of anybody. I remember going to school and I didn't - there wer
e some children coming from Rhydfelen and we didn't like those, they were very - I don't know, cheeky, you know, they'd call you names and put out their tongues and kick their heels, lift up their tails and say - oh hm, you know, shake the dirt off sort o
f thing you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh nothing. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I didn't have any hobbies as - as such. I - how do you mean in - sewing or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Or crochet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A lot of girls used to collect wild flowers and press them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, I did that too. Ellen and I, we did - fool - foolscaps full of them and clip them together, and sew them in yes, and press t
hem, yes we did a lot of something like that you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you do anything else in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
We learned for the scripture exams we had to you see and learn our verses, and we'd learn our own singing - we knew everything off by heart you
 see. Music, yes. Music and - and recitations - know quite a lot of some recitations, do you see, and all - nearly all Welsh you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, I had a pet lamb, Sally. Yes, and a chicken. Had a chicken and I lift her up and say now a good story. Oh cock-a-cock-a-cock}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 a-doodle - doodle, doo, she'd say quite a lot when I toss her and put her down you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the pet lamb?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And - oh the pet lamb, she was a naughty girl in the end. My sister brough
t - came along there one day with a baby in the pram. She went and butted the pram and all. My sister wouldn't come after until we put her in. But I taught her my - I was learning her to jump, I was going like this, now do that, come on Sally, up. And my 
mother said, it was - I was risk - risking my wrist you know, but oh I was none the worse any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You kept sheep did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, yes, she was a pet lamb do you see, and we fed her up from - from - lost her mother. Oh she was one of three perha
ps you see. And we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, we did quite a lot of gardening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We had - lovely kitchen garden - we had to. Yes. Plant - plant potatoes, well when I was young as I say I did quite a lo
t of outside work then do you see, quite a lot. Because I had to be out. Mm. I told you that before, yes. Well I don't know what was wrong, but - I was told to - keep out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was a good idea wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was I suppose, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you do any fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, not as such but - we used to play and catch tiddlers - when went to the well, but I tell you in that brook it was a brook that connected with the Taff fiver, and of course when the floods were my father used to pound that brook - brook
, and we'd catch a bucketful of salmon. Yes. Yes. Salmon, you know, coming up to spawn do you see, and then - and then - he - he'd turn the water onto the field, you see it would - the fish would come up and then pound it and push the water this way, well
 
he'd leave the water go, take a large milking bucket you see and he'd pick up the fish. And we'd give some to the - there were farms up there. When we killed pigs, we always gave - a good chunk of the meat to the other farms. Very neighbourly that way. An
d when they killed they gave us, well we caught fish. Otherwise that's as children I've got some fish for them. Yes, yes. Oh yes, have salmon look. No wonder we like salmon, no wonder I like fish.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You wouldn't have a lot of fish otherwise would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, not otherwise. No, later years when - just before I got married the fishmonger used to call then. But they'd made - made a road had been made through the place you see, but before then no we had to go and fetch it always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, perhaps we might go if - visitors, we'd take them around the fields or something like that yes, or go and see some of our friends or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I never bicycled, but I used to ride a horse. Yes. We had 
- we had three horses, Daddy, Betsy, and Uright. And - we had those, and Jet, but I never went on Jet, she wasn't - but I remember going down - we used to go down from the farm down as far as the Woolaford, and my brother on one see me on the other. Go th
e run see, can - canter down. Yes, yes. My mother used to ride, she had a - she had a lovely leather saddle, lady's saddle, see, when she was young of course.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She didn't ride later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 With who would you ride, your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A horse each, never together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you go to any theatres?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I told you - the first I went when I was - and I don't think I went for years after. No. I was eighteen or more befor
e I went to the pictures. Mm. And that was a fluke as - I went in the wrong night like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. Yes. Used to come down to the Park all concerts, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes. Used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would bring you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well my brother-in-law used to bring me - she - they were - they were belonging to the Cardiff Musical Etay is it, and I used to come every year. There were three concerts a year, I used to have one of them. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were lucky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were much younger and they were grown up and married I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Well Jane's husband - he always was here, and of courses he knew I was fond of music, so of course I used to go down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How would you get down there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
By train. No, I'd come down to Llandaf, stay in Llandaf, come from Llandaf they'd take me there see. Yes. Yes. Yes. One of used to go perhaps. My brother'd go - to one concert perhaps see, and once - one of the ot
her would go to the other and then I got one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about music hall, in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well I - I fancy I've been to one. I can't say more, and that was in Porth. With - with my Aunt Ellen, while I was a young girl. Oh dear yes, I was about twelve I could have been. Yes, and that's - all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Cinemas while you were still at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I couldn't say that I - had pocket money unless you had something - some - visitors wou
ld give us some money do you see, between us, never - no. We -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they be relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, friends, there
's one - a - the - a deacon's wife from the village who would - come up with us and there was another one, the girl that lived in the old mill house that we passed to go to the well, she used to come two days a week with us do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 But you'd pay her would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, she was paid, yes. Oh they were all paid. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There wouldn't be anybody else coming to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Supposing your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh well, one of the older girls would come you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about when she was having the baby, would you remember, you wouldn't remember when Eunice was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
I remember my mother - in bed with a new baby. Yes. I remember that. Yes, just remember it, yes. But see I was five then when Eunice was born do you see. And then there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What would happen then, who would look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - there - the woman used to come to my mother was - Jane Evans her name was, she used to - she was the midwife. Well her daughter used to come regular to my mother, a
nd another Mrs Morgan, she was - she used to come. If Mary Jane wasn't there - Anne was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So your mother would have outside help really?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She'd pay them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, yes, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No relatives or friends or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, not - I think everybody had their own business. But you knew where you were - when you had them down and paid for them, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 My mother - my mother's sister was in Porth. And - and her brother was in - Penygraig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 That's quite a way though isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, oh they wouldn't - they used to come down regular to see mother see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - I know they were there pretty often anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 As much as once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no, they wouldn't come as once a week, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It's quite a distance isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It is a distance, yes, yes. And the relations in Mysmoie, they were - there were two sons there, where my mother was brought up, from the
re she got married as I was telling you do you see, and they'd come down you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your father's first family, would they come and visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, they were coming every year. They were - they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Your father's first family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. They used to come regular. And when she had a large family - her - her husband was working on the - he was - what you - coal trimmer you call it, coal - loading from - from the - to the boats. Oh and they earned good money. Yes, yes. And she had
 ten children. And when they wanted to come home to see us and they came every year, he'd - hire a - wagonette. And he would be driving and she'd be by the door of the wagonette and the children there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they stay with you or just come for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh come for the day. But many of them came, one by one, in later years. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So they saw quite a lot of the first family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. We were - and we - that's when we used to go to Barry, in - we'd go to Barry every year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There was only Hannah now wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And Mary that was Mrs Turner, do you see, and Rebec - Rebecca.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you see much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - she'd died young. Yes, she had - she - she had two - three children. But she buried two children. And Ephr
aim was buried a couple of years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You wouldn't remember her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I would - I remember her coming yes, I remember her coming up to see mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And the boy of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, the boy, Frank Turner came to see us within about two month
s of his death, came round us as a family, yes, and he was nearly walking to slow to walk, he wanted to see us. And to think he was - mother was nothing to him. It was step-mother to his late wife. You know, but the connection was wonderful. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How do you mean friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Friends other than relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh yes, my - I remember my father had a man, we called him Evan Rededdan, I don't know what his name and what it was but they - we - when we were young we sp
oke of somebody like Martha, instead of saying Martha Thomas, Martha Maes Bach we'd say see, the name of the farm, do you see. There was quite a lot of people we never heard their surnames, when we were small do you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So he had a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh yes, Evan Rededdan, and he used to - used to - he had a wig, a man with a - with a wig, was, yes. Yes. Things - things like that you remember don't you, a wig, and he used to come and he always had a stick, square top - stick like this, and always he 
had two - hounds, hunting hounds, used to rear them do you see, and he would bring them down sit when he said in the kitchen there and talk. And there's another man - that used to come and see my father regular, was - John - John Davis - yes, John Davis h
is name was, Cyfaill John they called him, he went by the name of Cyfaill John, he wrote to the papers, he wrote to the Welsh papers, the Y Tyst is it, yes, he was a Baptist Minister, he used to come regular down to see us, I used to love to hear him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Your father would meet his friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, and Richard - Richard Thomas and William Thomas, they were both roadmen, they used to call there, and they were both deacons in Bryntirion chapel, see. It's the chapel - is threaded through everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your mother have friends like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes, Mrs Rhys Rhys you see and Mrs Morgan and Auntie Maes Maur, the auntie that came that used - was very friendly with mother. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your mother and father share the same friends or did they have their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh what was mother's was father's. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where would your mother see her friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Isn't it funny, I don't remember hearing them quarrel - no, no, not seeing eye to eye. That's strange isn't it? You know, today you hear of such a lot of inconsistency.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Life was so different wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. We lived on our own, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They didn't meet so many other people did they really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where would your mother see her friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 At - oh they'd come to the house, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would she go to other people's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh yes, she would go - if there was - if there was anybody ill now mother go and see how they were like you see and ask about them, how they're managing, see if she could help in some way or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When the friends came to the house would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh they'd never go from our house without a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they come on any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm. No. They - quite a
 lot of people - used to come now and come for the afternoon and go to chapel with us in the night and then go home from there see. Yes. Come and see - make it one journey you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well I know there was a Mrs Williams, of course she was very friendly, she was the mother of - she was the step-mother of the woman who used to come to sew for us for a month at a time, and her father was a deacon in 
our chapel. She was - that was one do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh quite a lot. Relations came, I remember - from Tanarivel they'd come, if there was a funeral anywhere - you could depend on it, oh they all go home, well call in to see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would neighbours call without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, no I can't say, we didn't have time to talk to them like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only just to see if there was anything wrong with them, yes, some trouble or something. You go and sympathise or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Talk. I can say that. Talk, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They wouldn't make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No. No. No. Well - you look at the difference see, daddy was twenty-nine years older than mum, do you see, as my mother said, when I married your father, I then had h
im for a husband and he was my father as well. Because I don't remember my own father. Do you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She used to tell you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Used to tell us. And then - I married a man - eighteen years - older than me. Well if I can do like my mother - I'
m all right. And I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were used to it weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I - I was - I didn't see a difference, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you think about your father being so much older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well it didn't dawn on us, we thought it was the right thing. We - we didn't - query it you know at all. We hadn't seen him different.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It's only since you're older you realize?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, you realized it such a gap do you see. But according to the life they led there's not a lot wrong with - it. I know that. No. And - he kept in good fettle. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He was eighty-eight when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And he was very active?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Very active as I say and he - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 he was bend - folding a he}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 dge right across the field, at eighty - at eighty-four. I remember seeing him doing that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well how do you mean that now? Some in the village now - we knew of th
em - and mother used to say, now don't you do anything with those, you leave them alone. They - they - they're up to no good. You know, perhaps they'd be going to public house or some - they - they kept a greyhound or something I don't know, there was no 
place for them. No. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 If they kept a greyhound?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Mother didn't believe in following dogs like that, you get like the dog. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There was no other difference in the area you lived did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. I don't think I know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What class or group do you think that you belonged to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Why - I - I don't know. We were - I'll say that my Auntie Jean told me from Tredegga, she said, she used to - I heard her telling my mother, Jean, we are somebody, aren't we? And I remember h
er saying that you see. Whether - she had - she was a Bailey when I remember her, when I was a girl, you know, and she'd been to Scotland, to Edinburgh, had her education do you see. We've got education, I mean - we're - that's how we're - bent, our lean 
you know, towards it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of people would you say belonged to the same group as yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well the shopkeeper was one of the same as ourselves. Yes. Adrian - Williams. And he was a bard. Yes. And - of course that's where we did our shoppi
ng, most of it, and we bought our sugar by the sugar loaf. Not - and of course when it came - father go and - to fetch if from him you see when it came, we had - we had a machine to cut sugar, cut it into squares and then cut it into cubes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You'd buy a huge quantity then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
You - you bought a loaf, a sugar loaf, which was standing high that way do you see. Yes. And that's where we got - if we wanted syrup we had to take a jug to get it. Yes. And he had it with a tap you know, a jug full and cover i
t with a cloth and bring it home. I remember that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What other sort of groups of people were living in the village then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And of course that man - if I keep on with that one, he - we'd go and fetch currants. Does your mother want currants? So
on for Christmas. Yes. Well tell her I've got a lovely lot cleaned. And we children would watch him cleaning them do you see, he'd have a big gwacar we'd call it in Welsh, s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12585436\charrsid15934717 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 eve, and he'd clean them, oh they were beautifully clean. To one after another you
 see. So that's - that's the kind of shop it was, and he was blending his own tea. Yes, and we bought it by the chest of twenty pounds at a time. You know, I can say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - to respect the aged. Give that. And especially - if they were church people, be the - same level do you see, and they were - usually they were deacons in the chapel, there were quite a number of them there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you ever told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, by the schoolmaster. By Mr Price Hawthorn. When we saw - the - resident - the gentleman of the village where we had school that was Hawthorn, Fairfield Hawthorn, when Mr Hamlyn Williams would pass, we - the boys had to bow th
en do you see. Remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was he the squire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
The squire of the place yes, Dr. Hamylyn Williams. Yes. He was a very kind gentleman, he'd come along - and he'd walk round, he'd visit the different farms he didn't own the farm - our farm or not
hing then, he used to come around as - as a - as a gentleman farmer would come around to see the stock, might be we'd have something to sell do you see, and - he'd come around and he'd go and he said, well I'm going to have a lie down now and he'd go to t
he front room and lie on the couch. Yes. And all he would ask for, do you mind giving me a bunch of raisins - to eat. Dr. Hamylyn Williams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was he a medical doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you show respect in some way, only just to that gentleman, no one else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - all the ministers, if possible yes, we used to entertain those. I don't remember the farm being without them. Regularly. Always.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was there anyone you would call sir, or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. I can't say we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents, by touching their cap or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I can't. Not markedly anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the village then who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the village? Well - the - the postmaster
, this Mr Williams that had the shop, he was the one and only shop do you see. He was our postmaster, he was the - you can nearly say, he was the organist in the chapel next door. And he was a deacon there. And he was the - secretary and my father was the
 treasurer of the chapel. And he was the - the pope of the village then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Why do you think they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I don't know, they were so active and they - they knew so much more than anybody else. They had knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And the one shopkeeper as you say he would associate with your family really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he associate with anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, well he was the - the shopkeeper of the area you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about other farmers in the district, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well we had a - there's another gentleman there, Mr Griffin the mill, he was a deacon in the Wesleyan chapel you see in Hawthorn about a mile away, we were very friendly with them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the clergy then, were there any clergy about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
We didn't have a resident pastor, but we had a - a gentleman, the Reverend David Morgan Jones - in Saron Treforest, he used to come down. And he used to come down practically every other Thursday afternoon, and he'd call at home fo
r tea and he'd come with us to the - well - to the service in the evening, the weeknight meeting we used to have, or one prayer meeting on Monday and - and the general meeting where we had to learn our scriptures so forth on the Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would there be a vicar or anything of the church there or only the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only the chapel, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There was no church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. The church was a good way away, but we were - daddy was friendly with those - Jenkins the vicar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the teachers in the area, who would they be friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I had a sister see, I had three sisters teaching. Yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any other teachers in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, another - a co-deacon with my father, they - they had a daughter teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would they be friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 With my sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 With each other really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any employers then employing people, there were no works really there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Nothing at all. Nothing at all. We remember the building of the power station Remember the foundation stone being laid of that you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Who would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - all the people - the farmers, yes, yes, all the farmers round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would there be any who wouldn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I don't know, we only see - as children we only knew the ones who went. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There was no church really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We - yes, we went - we - our - I remember father was friendly with him because he was a councillor, do you see, and daddy was a Guardian.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
In Upper Boat then did all the people have the same standard of living, or would you say that there were different groups, standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you mean some masons you see? Yes. Some colliers. Masons. And - I - don't know - I - know of some peo
ple - the members used to come to our chapel. But not their father, and they were extremely poor. Yes. Extremely, 'cos they were tenants of ours.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So there were different groups then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You say they were extremely poor, why would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well of course - those days - when they built, they wouldn't build - on the very cold and frosty weather, so if it was a hard winter - the mason didn't have a day's work, you see. But today they build all weathers don't they. Go see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember a family of masons like that who were badly off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. Yes, I - I do remember. But some of them are alive today and I wouldn't like to mention their names. Oh very very low. 'Cos I remember - yes, we - I remember my father passing there and putting a sack of swedes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 iving them a string of onions after do you see, yes, really poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You mean they didn't have enough food really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No, and then we would - mother would give clothes after us children do you see. Yes, quite a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you think that any group of people then felt superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
There was one - one party, they were living there, and we called the son Dai Ladi, because he was such a - a squirt as they say, you see, yes, he thought himself somebody. Yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Why do you think he thought himself somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I don't know, he - twisted his moustache this way you know, yes. We girls used to poke fun at him do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, we knew of some rather rough ones. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You did mention earlier that your mother frowned rather upon the families that kept greyhounds? Would you call them rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - we wouldn't - we wouldn't reckon with those at all. No. No, not at all, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember a distinction of any sort between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I can't say I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I don't remember them - making any difference. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I don't know what to say about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you think it was possible for people to move from one group to another 
or from one class to another? It may be that the village was so small that you felt you were all the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm. Yes - well I remember my mother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you feel that people were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I don't know, my mother would - if she - she'd go to 
chapel in the weeknight, and she'd invariably call to see somebody, goodness knows who. She'd call, she'd heard that poor there - poor there - the illness has struck them, she'd go and sympathise with them you see, she did - I know she did a lot of that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well the housekeeper of the man of the post office, oh - that's the daintiest woman I ever saw. I ever saw, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Why did you think of her as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well her hands were so delicate. Her hair was white and always wearing a mob cap with a - lily white fringe on it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Her appearance was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. Yes. And - I've got a - I've got a handkerchief now - that she embroidered - she gave it - she gave us
 one every one of us as children. And she made them - yes, I've got it. It's just a square piece with embroidery like that, half moon in it. I don't know where it is but I've got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child where you lived?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, the police used to come around regularly round the farms, to see if the dogs were licen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 ed do you see, and to see if - anything else. I remember being a witness - when I was a young girl of seeing a man passing through our yard 
- and my brother watched him, and by the time - he was crossing two of our fields, and he said, come here, he said to me - something gong wrong by here, I don't know what it is. It - he was going towards a little house, what we called the old mill, and - 
h
e - by the time we looked at him he had gone and then he was coming backwards, feeding - feeding chickens, they had just opened - it was before eight o'clock in the morning, we were milking do you see and going from one cow house to the other, and - he sa
i
d, look, he said, what's this? And we saw - he was throwing crumbs, having the chickens to follow 'til he came to our field. And when he got there he had a big stick with him, he gave it a blow, hit - he just killed it you see, screwed its neck, put it un
d
er his coat and came towards us, a path through our yard. My brother said, what's this now? So we went out, both of us went out, you know that story, yes, both went out and my - the man suspected we had seen him, he dropped the chicken and ran. I picked t
he chicken up and my brother caught him. And I had to appear in Llanduff court as a witness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 That was a bit of an ordeal wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes. But - but - I remember that - oh I was shivering like a leaf do you see, the end of the world I was
 going to a police court. And that's the only time I've been there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was there a policeman living in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. Yes. And they were - invariably they were Welsh police - policemen. Yes. Yes. And still we were friendly with them do y
ou see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 The policeman. Well - we thought they were all right, we were on very good terms with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh well I think they were very fair then, they seemed to - clo
se their eyes to some people you see, you know, first offence business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You did mention earlier that the farm was a Bute Farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was rented from the village?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Only when we went to pay the rent. They had - rarely come other time, but they - Sir William - not Sir William - what is he - I can't remember his name now. Oh I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you feel about them as landlords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They were ve
ry fair. Very fair. Yes. Yes. They were very fair. Yes. Even we - when we said we wanted something, you could depend on it you'd have it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well we looked after everything in moderation, until when - what you don't waste you'll never regret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He never was was he really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Yes, yes. That was - doesn't apply to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He was a Guardian wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I was going to ask did you ever get help from the Guardians, but he actually was a Guardian?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was there much work involved in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh quite a lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did he feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Of course - well - he kept going, he was at least six unbroken years you know that he was there, but he went to complain after because - the Guardians were meeting - on perhaps very fine - days when the harvest could be b
rought in, and the other farmers promised to meet him, oh you go Edward, we promise - but indeed they had as much as they could do themselves you see, until it went to and he gave it up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You wouldn't know how he felt about doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I - I'd bee too young. Yes, I do remember him going. Yes, I was very young though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, nothing like that. No, it was wonderful pea - wonderful peaceful. That's how I've been brought up anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They - they - had it for us you mean? Of course I had music lessons. Yes. Singing lessons you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 Where would you have to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 or would the person come to the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh at - Treforest. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember how old you were when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh I don't know - I left Hawthorn school at ten and a half to go to Mill Street Higher Grade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You don't remember how old you were when you went to Hawthorn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I went as soon as I could I suppose because there were others after me. It was five - was the - was the - time then. Yes. Didn't go b
efore you were five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you remember what time in the morning you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
About - by half past nine. To Hawthorn. But when I went to Mill Street we had to be up in Pontypridd at five to nine. And we had three miles to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about Hawthorn, how far was it for you to walk there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What would you take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well Welsh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 cakes. And sandwiches. That would be - perhaps cheese sandwiches you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you think of school? Of Hawthorn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - I liked it I must say. Especially
 - and I must say I can be - very thankful for one thing, that we had such a schoolmaster, Welsh, really Welsh, and - I - we learnt a lot of scripture with him, a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 
ll the ten commandments - the be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 atitudes and quite a lot of - different psalms as well, verses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 But besides that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We liked some and we didn't the others of course. It all depends how they took to us I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 If you did something that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well it would be a cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, I had the cane like somebody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 As well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Well on the hand you'd have it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You'd have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, but it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember why, what did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I must have been talking. Must have been. I don't remember doing any other thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes - yes, we did - we knew geography, you know, and when they were - in a hole they'd say, where is this, you - you know, you learnt it in school, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They'd ask you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would your parents ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, the only time I saw my father up there's when he was coming to fetch us and - and - and mother as well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would your father and mother ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We were on good terms with the - with - he was a deacon in Grasweyn do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So he knew the headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. And when he'd have a concert in the chapel he came as our chairman sometimes do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did the other children in the Hawthorn school come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - t
he - the - children of the village do you see, and children from Rhydfelen used to come down. And we never liked those. Oh - they seemed to - quarrelly, you know, quarrelsome lot they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, they did gang up a bit you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was yours a gang from your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, we'd have a few girls but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There would be gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any children who were left out of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well, I remember the teacher asking - one - his name is Bob Edwards, Roberyt Edwards, can any of you get me a good stick? And he got one. And indeed he; was the first one to have it. Yes. Yes. I remember that. He's alive today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You went on to another school then didn't you when you were ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. To Mill Street at ten and half I was really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You had three miles to go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How long would that take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well we - 
we used to start - we - when we were at - over the fields, we could go over the fields, for twenty past eight train used to pass, that's our mark. If we were up there just by the beginning of the tin works we were - sure of going in good time, we'd be jus
t in time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You'd have to go a bit earlier, at five to nine there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What time would you come home from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - the - the - the Cowbridge train started running, and if we could - we were let out in time, teacher would unders
tand, all those who want to go by train can go now. If you go a matter of - of a few minutes before the closing of the school and we used to catch the twenty past four train from Pontypridd to come to Treforest. Then walk from Treforest home then. That wa
s a little help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you catch that every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. And the last four months that I was in school, the trams started running in Pontypridd, and we used to go - come from Pontypridd down to Treforest by tram, for a ha'penny. And we used to go in
 the morning from there to - yes, yes, the last four months I was in school. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of school was that, was it a girls school or a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mixed. Mixed again, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you take your midday meal there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
It all depended. Yes, it all - because we used to go to - the restaurants in Pontypridd, you could have a cup of tea for a penny. And then we'd take our own food, but if mother would say - oh I haven't got a load of cakes, I've been
 too busy, got and buy it. You see, we'd buy, yes. Evans the Fountain Tea Rooms used to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You loved that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh, I loved it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you go often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, we'd go every Wednesday, 'cos - farmers came to market, and they were having them see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was a very decent school, I - I liked my life there anyway. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Some were very - kind, others were strict of course like in all mixed places, that's where I learnt crocheting. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Thats very useful isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well I - yes, I was - I didn't know crocheting and we used to stay in for dinner hour sometimes. We'd go and have our dinner, come back in plenty of time, not dilly about, dilly dally, and I remember seeing girls - one was doing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 humping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
 work, another doing a bit of - tatting I should think it was called by today, and crocheting, well I wanted to learn something. Well indeed - and the girl said, well you get a hook and cott
on, I'll teach you. And we - she did teach me. And I went to make a chain, and from the chain I grew to the - I remember one of the teachers, there's one old teacher always watching us do you see, and she asked me one day, what are you making Ruth? A }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 collaret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 , I said. This is the first attempt, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 collaret}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 . What colour is it to be now? You can guess the rest. I had opened it so many times it had gone dirty. Black. Well it was pretty dark. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did the teachers in that school emphasise certain things as i
mportant in life? You mentioned in the other school about the master being very keen on scripture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about in Mill Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, not so good. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did they emphasise manners or tidiness or punctuality or speech?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, punctuality, yes. Yes. Yes. I found nothing outstanding. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 If you did something the teachers disapproved of there what would happen?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We learnt quite a lot of - of part songs because we took part in concerts in - in the Town Hall. Yes, I remembe
r - singing there, as a girl. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they punish children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I never - the punishment was - stay in quarter of an hour and that was a real punishment for us - who had so far to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How would they punish the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I can't say. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of thing would you have to do to be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well the boys were only about - were there four or five boys in my - in my class following up and they were apart, there was a gap of desks between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of things would you have to do to be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well only stop in, I never - I never had - I never had lines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What offence would you have to commit to be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh copy from somebody else perhaps see, or talk. That's about all the damage I did anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork there in Mill Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. We used to have - our - reports, and - yes, mother looked after them more than father did though. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, I don't remember them visiting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they ever meet the teachers at Mill Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well they happened to know them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the other children in Mill Street, did they come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, there was one - girl in my class, she was - the daughter of Brynfa from Hendre Farm, and there were - there were other girls from over - the - by the Graig, towards Tonrevel, they used to come, the Richards they were, they were farming as well.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh they were the towns - town - yes, come from Kilvaneg, some from Harvard, different areas coming there. It was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of homes would they be from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - colliers. Yes, they would, colliers, yes. And I r
emember a girl - I was very friendly with a girl who kept the Red Cow in Hopkinstown, you know. Yes. Do you know her do you, yes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment form the others
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No, the only singlin
g I saw was if you could play the piano you were very much a - 'cos they always had somebody to play, especially if the teacher herself couldn't play you see. Yes, very helpful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any gangs or groups in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I don't - no, w
e weren't ganging up - not - not to my knowledge, there could be other gangs but we - we never got into - as soon as school was over our work was to get home, do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any children who were left out of things? In Mill Street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, not - not in the friends that I choose anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you go on to another school afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Fourteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well I think I would. I think of it to - especially today I would have. But of course I was wanted at home on the farm. Yes, I went to dairy class. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You mentioned that earlier I think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You enjoyed that didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, very much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you attend any other part time education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No other evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Only music, bit of music, sing - singing that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You did quite a lot of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I wish if I'd had more. Yes. Anyway I like reading now though. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, and especially Sunday school. Yes. And of course as I'm telling you our schoolmaster was 
- a religious man, he taught us an awful lot of the Bible. And then - yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did people go on to another school then? Was there another higher school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. No, the - the County School do you see, but we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You didn't have a chance to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, we were living the wrong side of the river. Yes. Not in - we were living in the Llantwit area do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So there was no opportunity for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No, not at Llantwit, not to the County.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever have a part time jobs or any means of earning any little money while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever have a job, a paid job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Never. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were just at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I did it on my own - on my own yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were never actually paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You just went home then and that was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm. Yes, that's it, yes. Well we were wanted, to work there do you see. There were always two of us home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have liked to have done something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well looking back no I don't think - I don't think I was fitted for anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Did you feel that in those days there were divisions of interest among workers? Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - we looked up to people who could do a good job of something do you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
What about life at home after you left school, what was it like, was there any change, was there any change in your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, not at all, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We were always - oh I don't remember calling him -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 There was no difference because you were grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Yes. We had a serving man, a good serving man there - staying with us. A
nd he used to come and go, he used to go back to Cardigan and come back to us after when he came - the fields distance from the houses he shouted, there's no place like home, and he'd come - yes, yes. Yes. He used to come with us to our - to the service o
n Sunday with us. We treated him and he - when he - the minister was there he was there on the same table. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You had quite a lot to do really didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes, yes, yes. Of course he used to go to chapel Sunday mornings and - school Sunday 
afternoon, and had to change your dress and - and go to do the milking. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would you have to milk then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, as soon as you were back from Sunday school, change our - have our tea, yes. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You would do milking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, and another sister and a brother do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What other jobs would you do on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
And I know - of course there were - there were the - the utensils. And we reared calves. And - there were pigs had to be done you see. We used to prepare the fo
od on Saturday. Only dish it out to them you see, yes. Quite a lot, and the same with the hay you know, used to put hay - handy, only pick it up on Sunday 'cos we believed in - Sunday was Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you spend your Sunday any differently when you were grown up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No, the same then now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, but we had scripture exams. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Every year they used to hold those did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Every year, yes. Yes. But we had to walk to - up to - perhaps Llantwit church to try the exam. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 The Arholiad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 The arholiad, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You don't remember what your views were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - my father was - was - what do you call it now - Liberal, yes, and so we were all Liberal. If father turns we all turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, since I married I voted. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You didn't vote before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No. And I haven't voted now for years now, I'm not in the - I don't happen to be in the same place when - when voting comes along. And I - but - yes, and the same people - when - when - somehow or other - oh who I would be voting for never c
ame in so there you are. 'Cos the Liberals have been pretty out goodness haven't they. Yes, they're coming on again I think perhaps I'll do it this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were you a member of a political party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever take any part in political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Nothing at all. Nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 After you left school how would you spend your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well the occasional concert, then going to Band of Hope do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Nothing different really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You said you used to crochet a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And your music, what about your singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. Yes, I'd stay to keep on learning 'cos - the one we bury - sister we buried in Llandudno, she used to play the organ do you see. And the sister younger - played. I didn't used to play much. S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15417729\charrsid15934717 inging, yes, duets and quartet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 s, yes. Do quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 An occasional concert. I used to go regularly to the Park Hall in Cardiff, every concert there, every winter, and
 the Rayleigh work, T. Ayleworth. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you go out regularly in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no, no. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you make any new friends then, after you left school now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. No, the same friends we were, yes, the - the farm girls that were around us, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You wouldn't make any new - like boyfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, very little, although there were plenty there mind but - I was in, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you take your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. Well though we - we children at home used to
 have the children of the next farm, they'd come for the day - a summer's day for to have a party, and we'd go back there perhaps, do you see, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about after you left school. When you were growing up, would you have any new friends? Would you make new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, I - no, I can't call them new, they were the same one is growing up with us you see, and there was a lot of relations do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - well - yes, Mary Williams, a
nd she was my age do you see in Sunday school and in every day school, and we got married within a year of one another, she was having children, and I went up to visit her at Ynys - to her farm, and she come down to me see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well they knew them all you see, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your parents expect to know where you were if you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well if we didn't we heard of it. Oh - now -
