\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about when she was bigger and you gave her a smack, what would you give her a smack for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh perhaps know king - I don't remember. I don't know indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How much did your husband have to do with the children when they were babies, under one year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Quite a lot. Yes, I must say. Well he - but always when I had a young baby he would see to the second one in the high chair. They were the ones were older then you see, and when - when that one h
ad got - I've seen him - dozens of times having his dinner, tea and that you know, he'd tell me, cut my meat up. Cut my meat up. And he'd hold the baby and eat his dinner. 'Cos there were four - four under six years. Do you see.
