Oh well, he used to take - when I had - when I had Ann, baby Ann - every afternoon he took little Ruth, she was only a year and ten months, took her on his arm up 
the road, but he never pushed the pram. No, I had a pram, but he wouldn't push the pram. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Well - I'm going back a bit now aren't I? Yes, they do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They used to think it was a shameful thing?
