\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. They - oh dear, yes, yes. 
It wasn't there you see. No. Well - no I - he preferred - it's more loving you know, a kiddy'd catch hold of his collar you know and be like this. And now my sister next door she was - par - partially deaf and dumb you know, she used to take - especially 
R
uth, she'd take her up the road sometimes if daddy was too busy, she'd take her up for a walk along the pathway, and if a car would come - she used to push my sister like this. She couldn't hear it you see, she push - and once she felt the child pushing, 
c
ouldn't talk, neither of them, she this one wasn't - the baby wasn't old enough to talk, so of course they - she knew that there was danger coming, so she went to the side. Oh likky Luth very good, she used to say, Likky Luth, she couldn't hear the sound 
to say Little Ruth see. No. Yes, but - we - she - we kept her see, between us, yes. Yes. She was in school 'til she was eighteen in Miss young's school.
