\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, I was pretty - handy on - the machine, do you see. I've seen the childr
en going to school with every stitch of my work on them. Yes. I used to make little stays and all for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your husband would he do anything like mending or making anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no, no, never. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Some men used to tap shoes didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh he couldn't put a nail in straight. No. He - as long as he had his piano -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He was so musical wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have new clothes or second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I don't remember we had second hand. No. But only from the 
oldest to the youngest - as we say. Yes, there was one of my - one of my sisters said like this you - did you want new clothes often? Well yes, by the time - my older sisters had worn it it was pretty worn out the time it came to me I had to have new ones
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Often the youngest is luckier than the middle ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, they become - mm. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would you have new clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When they'd gone to small for us I should think, yes, do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I've got lovely recollections of nice rig-outs. Yes I have indeed I must say. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you make them then or buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - we used to go to Hughes's the draper at Pontypridd. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You would buy your own clothes would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Buy - buy - buy the length do you see, and go - have them made that way do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You'd have them made up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, and there was another little girl, she was lame, she had hip disease and - she did all - nearly of all of my - children's clothes in Pontypridd. Yes, she'd make
 little coats - with astrakhan collars, oh they were pretty. Yes, very - but - babies clothes, I made baby - all those myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 But you would have a dressmaker really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. We used to go for an outing, take the three children, she'd measure 
the lot, I'd give her a piece - give her some material, she knew the size, and she'd write and let - somebody else, tell Mrs Jenkins I want to see her, and I'd give her enough stuff for say - for four dresses. Well she'd manoeuvre it and little bit she ha
d herself and she'd make five or six frocks coming back. She knew the money was right you may say, and she was - understanding do you see. Yes. Make the best of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about shoes, would you have new shoes or second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We never had second hand. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where would you buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
But I wore a lot of clogs. Yes. And - used to go over to Church village to have shoes made. There was a lovely cobbler there by Church village station, and then - and he said, when you've finished - when yo
u're tired of these shoes bring them back to me, I'll clog them for you. And I wore several pairs of clogs - on the farm that was you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did he mean by clog them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He'd - the uppers were real leather, soft you know, until - he'd put - the wooden base and - like a \endash 
 railway right on them do you see. A railway of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 The metal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, metal just this way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So you'd wear those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes. I never wore Wellingtons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you find clogs comfy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh they wer
e lovely, once you get used to them your feet are lovely. Go anywhere. Yes. You - you know - well - they used to say they'd one of the smartest feed going around there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you wear them at all after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only while you were on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, on the farm it was you see. Well I left when I was twenty-seven so of course - with having babies you didn't have wooden stuff after you see. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have new shoes after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I can te
ll you this much, I had moved from number six - to number three before buying a new pair of shoes. See? You can see I had a good stock coming from home. Yes. Yes, I hadn't bought a pair of shoes. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You must have had a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, well - mother was not so bad off you know like they say. As - not wealthy beyond but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You had a good trousseau did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, I did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about Mr Jennins, would he help you at all with jobs in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - put fire up see or something. Oh yes, yes, he always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He'd do it every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, if he - if time allowed, it - it - it must have been an awful push on him say a case come that wanted attendance at once do you see, and then he'd be going - or if he - the day it was the Gu
ardians meeting, he had to go to time then, but other times they were more or less his own time. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he help at all with the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He'd sweep round the back or - paths and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How about cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no. But he - he
'd - he taught me how to make Welsh rarebit, 'cos I didn't know the way to do it before, not as Welsh rarebit as they called it see. Yes. How to chop an onion. Oh - just like the galloping gourmet. Yes, indeed, he used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 He taught you how to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, onions and so forth, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was his Welsh rarebit something special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - the onions you see, he did it first in the frying pan, and then he'd put the bacon and he'd cut that up after, after that was really cooked, a few sli
ces of cheese on top, and pepper and salt and - oh he was doing business then Yes, that was it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Not remember. But he - if he wanted a supper, he wanted what he called \{BLANK\} oh later - later years, and when he was ill yo
u know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
It was only soaked bread. In - in tea, strain the tea you see, soak the - and sugar, and - and he wanted a little chunk of cheese with it always. And then we didn't hear of him all night after. It was easy to sleep on you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So they used to call it didn't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So, yes. Yes. Bara soacan we called it, the - the name itself said what it was you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about washing, would your husband help you at all with the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, very little. Because I used to keep a little maid. And - he - he - you know, he was lucky like this, or I was lucky. He'd go around and of course there was a large family, what are you doing with these children, Mrs - Lyons, one woman was
. Well I don't know if I knew of a place, would you like to start in our house? My wife will put her on you know by our place. And they always put on weight with me. Oh yes. Yes. And then they went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So you were lucky like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. That way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about decorating the house? Would your husband do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh no. No. But I've seen me, I - I've seen me papering, and I - I have done a little graining - coloured room and grained the doors. Brush graining. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh paid everybody, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Any improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - in - in what way do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would your husband make any improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh nothing. No, no. No, nothing - paid it was, it was a man - a Mr Griffiths we had
, he was very whatsname, and the Shales from here, years ago, and Williams Tenant, they used to - know - know him - know him in the - know him in the pulpit, I didn't know him as a man do you see. Yes. Yes. Yes. That way you see. Yes. And in the second - 
i
n the third gamanfa - and listen to this, according to the books we have bound - I - I've bound all his programmes do you see into two volumes - these - the standard lamp says forty-one years, for he - that he conducted the do you see, and here - Llywydd 
-
 Mr John Morgan, Hopkinstown and certain dates, Trysorydd, Mr William Jones Cifynydd, that's Cifynydd Mr T. Griffiths Preswylfa, 1906 - 1922. There is no mention of soloists before 1915. Now see. Now that 19 - that's six the - the gamanfa was, yes - in th
e gymanfa in 1915, these are the soloists, Miss Ruth Morgan, Upper Boat. That is me, yes. Miss Bronwen Thomas, Gyfeillion. And - that's - Hopkinstown. Miss Jennie Griffiths, Penuel. Who survives, she says see. Thank you for the stamps and everything. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So that means you first knew him as a conductor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 So - 1906 do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were performing as a soloist then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 As a solist in 1915. Now, we did have a - these are on - the names on the programme. That's how she was able to pick it up. 
We had gamanfas before we know in our - as I said, he wanted a change like, make a difference in things do you see, and - Morfudd Owen sang the concert - the one before me, because - I remember I told you before. Yes. Yes, because I was - I said, what are
 
you having me for, I said, an Irishman's rise I said. And he told me, well look she's been in college and learnt music and all like that. Well yes he said and I've only been on the farm. Never mind, put Morfudd Owen under a cow, what does she do? See? Yes
, that's what he said them see. But of course, all due respects but that's the way - he - he pulled me into singing see 'cos I was having lessons with him see. Yes. Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did Mr Jenkins help you with the children at all? Would he dress them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - well - he might put their coats on ready to go to school to see that they're in their outdoor clothing, nothing - no other - no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he read aloud to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he tell stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, he had quite a bag of stories for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - well he had to when I was - I was at home one year a whole year, never went - anywhere.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would he look after the children if you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. He'd - I'd go to town or go to concerts, something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have any regular little household tasks for the children to do to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, if they - one had to dust and one had to do something else and reach things and - you know, help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What time would the children be put to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Not very early, I must say, because we had Band of Hope, Band of Hope at half past six, for an hour, by the time they had come home, this, that and the other it would be towards nine often see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they be put to bed by themselves, or would one of you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh we - I'd go with them. Always, yes, always see them in bed, they had a good wash ready for the night and it was a lick in the morning. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did the children share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. They'd - they'd two in a bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember what the sleeping arrangements were in number three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I had - one, two - I had three - double beds. And one single. I had two singles. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You and Mr Jenkins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, we - oh we were together, yes. And then - Gwenllian and Ruth. And Ann and Jane, do you see, that's how they were - as they grew up do you see, and they'd a very pretty cot, with elephants and kangaroos - elephant used to say, you know, yes, elephant.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your step-daughter, would she have a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She had a single bed in the front - little bedroom. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She was in a bedroom on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, and then - she never slept with my children. No. H
er habits weren't too good. No. I'm admitting that. And you know, the - it - it would - affect them do you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was she long with you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She was with me - she was - 'til she was twenty-one. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She was still in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, she was in school - she - ordinary school and then she went to - have shorthand and typing. And then she went to the shop I was telling you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She wouldn't help the children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - she - they wouldn't reach bed I'm afraid. Oh 
- I could say - I could say wonderful stories about her, and she's still alive you see. She's still - but she's lost her husband. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What room would you use to bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We'd got a bathroom. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would they bath,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - going to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would it be every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, not every night, no. Well - it all depends - summertime you know you get dirtier - but it - it was a weekly business at least. A weekly hair wash regular. 'Cos my sister-in-law used to say, you wash them far too
 often, but they were lovely and clean, I didn't care who came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When did the children have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where were the meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 If we were only a few of us in the kitchen. And - I had - by the stove handy that
 and pantry, that's very handy, but otherwise - in the other room, tea in the other room, supper perhaps it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Supper mainly in the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where did you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What sort of cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I did have - oven and a fire. And - and - I had a stove as well. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh only the oven. And - and I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A coal range was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A coal - coal, and a little gas jet on the - on the hob, for the kettle do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh, as soon as we got up, you see, ready to go to school by nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What members of the family would be present when you had breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 The - yes - 1918, we'd - only daddy and I and - and - and the daughter. Margaret Mary. Maggie May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Only you three is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm. Mm. And see her off first you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Before father went off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Before her father, yes, she had to walk to Treforest you see. Yes. Or catch the bus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you have to eat for breakfast and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Bread and butter or toast with tea it was always. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - yes, yes, we'd have - in the winter it was porridge, made in the - the night before, you see, made night - so it wa
s thoroughly cooked, and it was kept on the hob covered and it was - wasn't cold after do you see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have anything different on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And I never boiled the milk. No. No. Never boiled the milk. Others seemed to have boiled it, b
ut I never did unless it was to - keep it from getting sour 'cos there were no fridges then see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were lucky the milk didn't go sour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. Well keep it in the - a shadowy place, you know, the shadow of the house is cold usually, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have anything different for breakfast say on Sunday or any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about dinner hour, who would be there for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Sunday you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, any day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - daddy used to come - oh but he'd come in all
 hours into the house, yes, I had to keep his dinner hot do you see. Or I'd wait for him perhaps when the children were in school do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your step-daughter, would she come home to dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. She took hers with her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would the next meal be, would you and Mr Jenkinds have lunch on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Well it was - I'd eat with the one that was happened to be there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you make a meal when they were getting home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no, see, no, well
 - I was very fond of making cake, and I would whip up some round cakes or some pancakes or some - and I was very fond of making pickelets, they were easy - easy to eat you know and everything, and - and on the - on the bake-stone see. Had a big old bake-
stone, and I've lost it now, I really - I lost it in the moving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You'd have that for tea then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have a meal in the evening or what?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 That would be our meal - tea with it do you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What would you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh just tea then. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have anything else then in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Like - like - a - a large cup of milk between the children or a large cup of coffee - not coffee - cocoa - between the children, I didn't used to give them too much to drink to go to bed. I thought of myself see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How do you mean now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were Sundays different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - oh we had a cooked dinner on Sunday. And of course I kept the ministers for years, so they had
 to come - we were all going to chapel and you come back - and - when - I don't know - the dinner came the same anyway. \{BLANK\} it was always, especially the war time, you know, we weren't have an extra meal you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When you married the rations were very poor weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh I made it for years, used to buy fifty-six pounds of flour at a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh I've made - I can - I can say honestly I've made as much as a hun
dred pounds a year, because I had a love - I had lovely apple trees, and I had - plenty of gooseberries, oh dear so many gooseberries, and redcurrants, white currants, blackcurrants, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Not so heavy, but I - I would - I would make per
haps one pickled cabbage just to say it was there like, but I used to make chutney. Very fond of chutney 'cos we had - onions, that - that wouldn't die you know, those - pickling eggs, and another thing - the lady next door, Mrs Pritchard I told you, she'
d give me bowls of tomatoes, that they didn't want, they grew far more than they wanted you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about wine, would you make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Ah yes, I made wine. But I haven't made it now since I lost daddy. There was no point in it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 But when you first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, I used to do - I only made the elderflower. Never made any other kind 'cos it was like champagne. There is a bottle in \{BLANK\}
 now. I wouldn't like to drink it 'cos it's too potent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about beer? Would you make any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh small beer, yes, herb beer, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Like your mother used to make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh no. No. No, never did it. No, no. That's gone with her, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Bottle vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes, and I used to make apple rings. Apple rings, yes, I've a frame - hanging on the ceiling, like an umbrella. Like a - and I'd make them, did them in salt water and put them there, you know, quite -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Drying them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, it was a big apple, an
d I'd do them, I'd make a bowl of stewed apple, perhaps two plates of tart, and with all the apple stumps - I'd make jelly. Because the - the jells with - the more pips are in it you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How do you mean, grow them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you bottle any or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I have done kidney beans, but - no - didn't have the surplus to do them, we used them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you grow your own vegetables and fruit or would you buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I used to grow, I remember going to
 the old greengrocer coming, Johnnie Moore coming, any vegetables today Mrs Jenkins? No indeed, we've got peas and beans and potatoes, no, not today thank you. Well - you grow everything then? I don't think you grow bananas he told me. I said, no, come on
 
then, give me a couple. Oh he was a good - and that's a man I can say about - you don't get it everywhere. You don't get it very often. Doesn't - if I said, no, not today thank you, thank you very much, he'd say, as if I'd given him a - a tall order. Oh h
e - he was a - very dear old chap, yes. There was a way about things you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about tinned vegetables or tinned fruit? Would you have anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes. We were very fond of tinned fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Dried vegetables or dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I - yes, I made - dried apricot jam, made a lot of like that do you see. They were the only things I do, dried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. Oh I did want to keep chickens. But we knew the people - both sides wouldn't be willing for it,
 and - I'd have loved to have kept a little pig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You were used to it see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. Yes. I remember when Eunice was ill in bed with pneumonia, we had a - a litter of pigs born, I carried two up in my apron upstairs for to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How many times a week would you eat meat, this was the end of the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. Oh well we used to have it pretty good. Yes. Used to have - there was always meat to be had - in the first war you mean now, yes, always on a Wednesday, yes, well we had to go 
two miles to the butchers. But there was one butcher, the son of Brynfab the Bard, he used to come - he was in the same class as me in school and he knew I'd be living there he'd call, anything today Ruth, he'd say. Yes, what have you got \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 call you know. But it wasn't a regular business, you see, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often would you think you had meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well we always bought meat - meat on Friday for the Sunday. Yes. And a good chunk at that mind. It was all meetings you see - what - what I used to buy to cook them in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Not very often. Anything - corned beef was the only tinned meat we knew of then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about extra meat from poaching, like rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. I never tasted rabbit until Jane was married. That's the first time I - tried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever have to go short of food so that your husband or children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. I've been very well fed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did your husband need to have larger helpings of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well of course - it was the habit with us if we had an egg the husband had two, do you see, so you know - what else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the children, were they-allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well through and through, it didn't - yes - now, get on with it, don't talk
 it was you see, and - if it was they had to go back to school that afternoon do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or would they have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Eat what was going, usually. But one of them 
liked the yolk of an egg, the other liked the white. It was all - it was lovely. And funny the one who - who chose the white, it was all right that she ate it, and it was all right that the other had the yolk. Strange isn't it, and mother never gave us - 
more than half an egg until we were ten. Yes. Well I was - I was carrying on the same then you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What was your attitude if the children left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - if - if it was good, put it in the pantry and you must ea
t it before you get the next meal. Yes. Or perhaps if some - they'd have gone in the pantry and finished it off themselves while we were waiting for the next meals and that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Could the children wait until things on the table like the salt were offered to them or could they ask for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh they took it themselves. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, usually it was - anybody want more, it is her for you, if they would or would not - there was no pressure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they hold the knife and fork in a certain way or sit in a certain way? Would you make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well - when we say had our food in the kitchen I had a little bench there - we'd pull the table out and two of them sat there. One - I sat there, daddy was here. The baby perhaps was - the baby there in a high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were they allowed to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. One thing at a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would the members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh we usually - all together, or just - according - they've got to go like you see you know, to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did all the family sit for the meal at the table together, what about your step-daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you all sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well, she was there. The two children here do 
you see, one on the edge here and one with daddy on here do you see. And I had the table - I had a flap put on the table, longer to come out here to make it a long table you see, when we were a few that flap was down. I had it put on especial. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you all sit in the same places always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, they knew which - which was going first.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How would the meal be served, by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Me - oh me really yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How would you serve it, would you put it all out ready or would you have just the 
meat done or would your husband carve the meat at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, daddy never carved it. Never. I did it all. Yes. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you put it on the plates ready?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - it was on the end of the table 'cos - and I sitting there. Where is your 
plate? Then - perhaps he'd fetch the potatoes out, potatoes in a dish. Yes. I had two dishes like - they were like open tureens they were, with the bordered edge to them I remember. I remember those - as if it was yesterday. And I had another pair after w
i
th handles on them. On the side. And I put them in the wash one day, oh I was stupid that day, and I drew the hot water - to - put some powder put over. I went like this - to turn the powder in the bowl see, and - you know there's a little bit where the o
v
erflow comes out of the bowl and little bit, as I was doing that I - I hit the handle up and I hit the next before I'd realized. And I did it with them both mind, hit the - the four handles off, that stupid thing to do wasn't it? I remember as if it was y
esterday. They were a pair of cream ones. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about feeding the children when they were too young to feed themselves, where would they sit and who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Oh I - I did it usually, daddy or me. And I had a spoon - a baby spoon with a - a fork as well, they - have you see them? Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 A spoon and pusher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Yes. And - no I didn't have a pusher. No. No. Yes, yes, yes, no, and they would scoop it, but do you know what, the - I took it too - to Claire Lawn, for Ann's children, both were left handed, they couldn't use it. It was the right handed spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would your husband feed the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, any time, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the older children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh they - they'd feed themselves then see, oh - you put it for them they'd eat it, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Gwen wouldn't help the others to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, no, everyone for themselves see - you had to tell them you hurry up or else she'll have it, come on, quick quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When would they join in the family meals, the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
You mean in - in a chair? Oh well - I can't remember now, no, they did come in - in due course like see, 'cos I remember the preachers would come there \{BLANK\} they'd say see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When your children were young did you feel that there was a right way or a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well I - only one way I had I was doing as my mother taught us. We were all taught to sit down, we have the Sunday morning, with a couple of ministers, we kept them for years on the farm you see, the
re's nobody else. They'd come on the Saturday and go back on the Monday, see. You know, it was very - you can't realize it today perhaps do you see. That was the way - we didn't see it strange. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 That was all you were used to wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, y
es. Mm. Yes. At first - when you did get married it was only us three, my husband and - Margaret Mary and myself. Of course we went to chapel three times see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up children or different ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well we co-operated all right you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, not so much, we noticed their advancement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was it difficult to you having the little girl already there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I'd a lot to teach here I can tell you. I did. I had a lot to teach her - yes, you'd be surprised. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was it difficult for you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - I didn't - you know - I - I don't know what I can say about her. She's still difficult if you only knew her history, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was difficult for her probably wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
It was, you know, she - she had been brought up with her mother and the grandmother, they never left their grandparents do you see, and the wife had been - their mother was buried, well they still had the grandparents do you see and
 of course the instil very old ways about them do you see. And - and I - yes, but I think she - he may a big difference in their life to come to me because they've - lived, between you and me, very very skinny. If there was one tomato it was a slice for e
verybody, not one - not a tomato each, I know that's a fact, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It must have been a tremendous upheaval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And for you as well to wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It - it was - to see the difference in her, she'd say, no, that'll be all, that's enough 
for me, you know, and she wouldn't eat this and wouldn't eat that, but she came to eat everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you discuss it with your husband at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No, well he could see that she was - having the better of it you see, yes. It was difficult mind sometimes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You weren't all that old really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. No. And to have - yes, to have a girl -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Four - fifteen - fifteen, sixteen she was then. And the other one was nineteen see. No, the other one was - twenty. Sh
e was fourteen the - the youngest girl. Until - and they'd had their way like do you see most likely and - the oldest -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did she feel about the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - oh they wouldn't wat - everybody wanted to nurse it see. Yes. Yes. Oh they were very good that way mind, yes. Yes. I must say.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It wasn't worth talking to anybody don't think. I had to make up my own what\rquote s name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Was your mother alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, my mother. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
My mother saw everyone of them because when I had my last baby, she asked me, what's this one's name to be. I said I didn't know exactly, we hadn't settled the - they wer
en't in such a hurry to give the baby a name then. You had the six weeks to realize - that you'd had a girl and not a boy. And - in - then - and she - well I - I mentioned a few names. Oh, she said, my little name is not good enough for your children. I t
o
ld you before did I. Yes. For your children. And when I heard that of course that put the - well of course we had - buried a sister by the name of Jane, and you know, she was a - she was a bit of the flower of the family, she was so fair, and delicate tha
t
 she died at - thirty-two, see, and mother - she had buried her do you see, well not many years before, 'til I thought perhaps it was hurting her to hear the name, Jane, call Jane, Jane. She asked for it and then she had it. Yes, oh - oh she was very plea
sed. And the last winter mother die - mother lived, she had her photograph taken out in the - in the garden just like that do you see and the baby on her lap and snow around them. And a little snow in the middle - on the baby, so that's Jane, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often did you see your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh - she - in the last years she never - she was - every day she came into my house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about when you had the children small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well she wasn't living in number four when I had Gwenllian. She hadn't come there then. She hadn't retired then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How often did you see her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Well I used to go over and see her - until - I went - I couldn't go over, I went over the - the farm every day to fetch milk. 'Cos there was no milkman calling. I - yes, and I
'd - 'til I - went disabled, I'd milk a couple of cows for them. Yes. And daddy was working see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You used to go every day to the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ask her advice on bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 She told me what to do, like in - in the way of dressing them, what to get and everything else you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you and she have the same ideas on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well - I did everything she told me. I didn't cross it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about your mother-in-laws?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I never had one. No. No. That's one good Godsend isn't it, they tell me. I don't know whether you've been as lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
What about some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children now? Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Give them - some different advantages you mean? Well of course they had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you really feel you wanted to do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I wanted them to - to - to learn, I could - couldn't give them enough books do you see, no. To learn - and to learn to l
ook after them, and if it's - I - yes, they could read them while I was looking. Not - not for the other one to tell her, now keep away from there she's having a read, or I'd tell one to go - to go to the other room and have a read, go - your father's in 
there doing his - his work, you go the other end of the table, and then he'd see that they were doing their homework and so forth see that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 The children? Oh yes, what is the matter, who has bumped you today. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I wanted them to - be obedient didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When the children were young did you and your husband ever manage to leave them so that you could go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When they were very small? Well I left them because I - next door I had my mother and my sister next door, do you see. They were in -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 They would come in would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You and your husband could go out if you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 We could go, yes. I'l
l tell you what wee did do, we used to go to matinees on Saturday afternoon, we heard Ben Davis in Cardiff, Sir Thomas Beecham, Clara Butt, I know - all those - Pallagouchi - went down with - you know, yes, and - Harry Lauder - Harry Lauder after - oh we'
d
 have a good afternoon like that see. Yes, and then they'd - it was daytime when they watched the children then we were back to have a meal in Cardiff, and - 'cos I remember going to - I don't know - to the Sandringham I think we went after, well - he sai
d, well I want a good feed, we were in a hurry having our dinner. So we'd gone down by \{BLANK\}
 then, and - we'd go to the Sandringham. What shall we have? Poached eggs on toast, he'd say, we haven't had an egg for a couple of days. And when two eggs came to
 me I couldn't - I - to think I'd - that's the first time I think ever ate two eggs. Isn't it strange? I was so shocked to be given two eggs. I remember it. Oh but I enjoyed myself, you see, and the lovely atmosphere then, I remember, coming down with him
 
after and we went into the - to Samuel Halls. There were dresses - now - which of these do you like? And I said, oh I like the red one but it will be too much for us. Let us go in, he said. And I had a red silk frock, knitted frock. Two piece. But you kno
w
, it's not - we're not lucky people to have red. No. My sister bought a red costume now, and my sister's daughter died, within - within a fortnight of having it. And I remember - Gwen didn't live more than about five weeks after I got that rig out. I went
 - you - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You never liked red then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
No, I took it - and it was a beautiful rig out. So he said, now, here is a present for you. Mm. Yes. I had a - I had a good old partner. I had a good old partner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well if they had got a bit - big, they could, yes, if the conversation was - is getting a bit what\rquote s name well we'll drop it now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 That - they should g
o to - to chapel, and learn. To learn and to obey. Yes. And to obey their teachers, I never - I never went up to the school for one of them. I don't know whether they were good or bad or whatever they were, let them find their own way. If the teacher was 
- well I never had any cause. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you tell them they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I remember my mother telling them - if they do hit back to do it but to - no, I don't - I - I don't remember doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any children that you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, there were children up the street. Yes. Had to leave them alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Because I don't know, they seemed to be - you know, there was a - they was - there was a quarrelsom
e pair, they were the - the Gibbons - their names were, Gibbons, and one of them came down to do some business behind this - this - this street here that's opposite, I don't know what's the name - Evertruda is it? She was - do you know what, she was caugh
t
 - she was going about and going to Howell's and - and ordering a rig out, and ordering this, that and the other and giving the - the lady's name, they - they - all the children turned out, and I - and I was saying now when I heard that, that's not so man
y years ago. That's since I've buried daddy - I was saying, well we weren't far wring then in our estimation that I wasn't willing for the children to play with them. Do you see, there was something telling me, to keep - keep away from them. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen? You did mention that you'd give them a little smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would your husband ever give them a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 I never saw him do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 It was you was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. If it was - I did it, yes. 'Cos I - I think - if he did it would be something very extra, I think he'd be too heavy with it see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember any particular occasion when the children were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And I don't remember my father ever doing anything to us, my mother did all what was to be done. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Do you remember any particular occasion when you punished the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Not outstanding. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you say that the children received the ideas that they had about how to behave from both of yo
u, or did you or your husband play the most important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well I think they listened to the conversation at home. And they knew it you know. And you'll do as you\rquote re seeing done won't you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 When the children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Oh we might - well that'd be a day for pancakes. Yes. I remember Easter time now, I'd always make some little cakes now - in - little nests, eggs in them and they come with - with desiccated coconut and brown - you know, to it's -
 it's supposed to be straw. I'd - all - I always did some, I went with the - with the fashion, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would the children have presents on their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes, always a - a - an article of dress usually, and then perhaps a toy or a book or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would they have guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 
Not very often. We - we - we were a lot of relations, my sister had two daughters living down the village and they - when - if they wanted to play they were up in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Can you remember what you would do on Christmas Day, you and your husband and your step-daughter it would be wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. Yes. Wel - yes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You'd just had the baby in 1918 hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes. I couldn't do much th
en could I. But I have a very happy Christmases when the children were growing older. Mrs Pritchard used to come in every Christmas morning, she'd bring something, some sweets or something like that she'd bring, and she wanted to see the presents the chil
d
ren had. Oh and she Well he - I don't know, he said, he could - but it was like this, the teacher would come to the house and teach them, teach two at a time. Well one now, she'd come back and go back with her own lessons, then the other goes in. And then
 
- he'd come home, perhaps he'd have his supper, he had been out - Ruth he said. He'd get up from his meal, he'd say, he's come - he's come - now - play that again. And she'd play it. That is not what Miss Vevan told you. No, daddy. Oh yes. And he'd - now 
he'd sit down, play it, oh yes she said. Now she'd have been practising wrongly all the week. But he - he watched - he did, he kept always on them yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 You sang didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you help them sing as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh he had a lovely tenor voice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you ever make music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Yes, we sang when we worked, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh that we go a Maying, you know that song, you that, yes. And Hywel and Blodwen. Yes. What were you saying now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you have any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Music - music books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Ordinary books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh yes, we had a nice bookcase full of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And I had all Dickens. Yes. And - and the musical educator we had all those. And we had - 
the Geiriadur Beible, I had all those. Buying them - at a time and getting them bound you know, that's what we do. That's what I was doing. Yes. He didn't have them when I got married, he's had those after having me. And - but he had music ones because he
 had a lovely presentation from Cilfynydd of a lot of music books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Would you take newspapers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Always the Western Mail. And the Pontypridd Observer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And the Cenhadur. Yes, Trysorfa Fach. Took it for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Where would you get them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Through the chapel the - Trysorfa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 What about the newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Oh delivered by the door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 And books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Well the books we - yes, we took Tit-Bits quite a lot. And things like that. And I used to like the Woman\rquote 
s World or something like that see but - didn't have much time to read those though. But it - I liked them for the recipes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1406435 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 No. The children did. The children did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10968918 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14815767\charrsid15934717 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children?
